of these , over one million were left homeless in the immediate aftermath .
in the devastated urban areas , the displaced were forced to squat in ersatz cities composed of found materials and donated tents .
looting — restrained in the early days following the quake — became more prevalent in the absence of sufficient supplies and was exacerbated in the capital by the escape of several thousand prisoners from the damaged penitentiary .
in the second week of the aftermath , many urbanites began streaming into outlying areas , either of their own volition or as a result of governmental relocation programs engineered to alleviate crowded and unsanitary conditions .
